   {:e #blake3 "327a2255b91151867898cf71bdf3d291cc0fc7c8241aa0bc6958991fa5d56163" :a :db/ident :v :harvest/session-braid-user-1774059730 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "327a2255b91151867898cf71bdf3d291cc0fc7c8241aa0bc6958991fa5d56163" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-03358e061ba228bf; Session entity: :recon/trace-3e1e85022a917b31; Session entity: :recon/trace-561b72d6e2e6a664; Session entity: :recon/trace-8df6aa8648e010a8; Session entity: :recon/trace-35591eb6279293a6; Session entity: :recon/trace-c7f7bc31879ca080; EPISTEMOLOGICAL-CHAIN: The system has four layers forming the complete knowledge pipeline: Intent (observations, decisions — what the agent experiences), Specification (INVs, ADRs, NEGs — what's formally agreed), Implementation (code, traces — what's built), Behavior (test results, witnesses — what's verified). These recapitulate the epistemological chain from subjective to empirical: Intent=subjective, Spec=intersubjective, Impl=objective, Behavior=empirical. Three adjacent boundaries connect them: (1) Intent↔Spec (crystallization — observations become spec elements), (2) Spec↔Impl (implementation — spec elements get code+tests), (3) Impl↔Behavior (verification — code gets witnesses). The coherence state is fully characterized by the tightness of these three links. F(S)=1.0 means all four levels are aligned. The reconciliation taxonomy maps directly: Epistemic+Axiological divergence = Intent↔Spec boundary, Structural divergence = Spec↔Impl boundary, Behavioral divergence = Impl↔Behavior boundary. The other divergence types (logical, aleatory, temporal, procedural) are second-order — they operate within or across these primary boundaries. CRITICAL FINDING: braid observe lives at the Intent↔Spec boundary. Currently this boundary has ZERO per-transaction measurement. The 252 untested INVs gap and the crystallization backlog (32 observations) are both symptoms of unmeasured boundaries. TRACES TO: SEED.md §2 (divergence types), SEED.md §6 (reconciliation taxonomy), INV-BILATERAL-001 (bilateral convergence).; Session entity: :recon/trace-1bc19ee115005a64; Session entity: :task/t-070864f1; SESSION-PROGRESS-DASHBOARD: braid status shows cumulative metrics (P(t)=0.60, F(S)=0.67) but no session-level deltas. The data exists — :session/start-fitness, :session/start-datom-count, session_boundary computation. Missing: per-session view in status output. FIX: Add session-delta context block to build_status_projection and build_terse: 'session: +14 tasks closed, +312 datoms, F(S) +0.02, P(t) +0.03 (2h 15m)'. Implementation: read session start attributes, compute deltas against current values. Pure display addition — no new state, no new invariants. With metabolic delta-crystallization, session progress can also show: Δ-cryst cumulative, Δ-impl cumulative, giving directional progress insight. TRACES TO: INV-INTERFACE-008 (LLM surface optimization), INV-BILATERAL-001 (bilateral convergence).; Session entity: :recon/trace-989733a77f1e6988; Session entity: :recon/trace-7c3852eb9f114d0a; SESSION-030 DOG-FOOD: 41 tasks closed. Key friction: (1) harvest alert fatigue during rapid task execution — 10+ 'overdue' warnings in 2 hours. (2) 18/41 tasks were already-implemented — system tracks creation but not fulfillment-by-side-effect. (3) Per-task store reload for closing is O(n) when batching would be O(1). (4) F(S) immobile at 0.67 despite 41 tasks — P(t) was the only progress signal. (5) Old task title bloat persists — TAP-SPLIT only helps new tasks. Key positives: (1) R(t) routing gave clear starting point. (2) P(t) metric immediately useful — visible progress. (3) Seed context from session 029 eliminated re-orientation. (4) CRB-PREVIEW would have caught the 18 already-done tasks at creation time. (5) --attest on done forces articulation of evidence.; Session entity: :recon/trace-c19c85664555a2bf; Session entity: :recon/trace-6541117ef69f0e92; Session entity: :recon/trace-2cc48b98bb708316; Session entity: :recon/trace-a5003b3776ef4cf1; Session entity: :recon/trace-9859ba68163f5763; HARVEST-ALERT-FATIGUE-ROOT-CAUSE: During Session 030, harvest warning fired after almost every command during rapid task execution (15, 17, 19, 21, 23, 25, 27, 29, 31, 33, 35, 37 tx warnings). Root cause: INV-HARVEST-005 presupposes uniform information density across transactions — every tx equally likely to contain harvestable knowledge. This is false. Task closes carry zero novel information; novel observations carry high information. Current urgency function U=max(s1,s2,s3,s4): s1=tx_count/dynamic_threshold (quantity), s2=minutes/30 (time), s3=exploration_count/3 (value), s4=k_eff<0.15?1.5:0 (emergency). Signal 1 dominates during batch operations. CRITICAL FINDING: surprisal_score is IMPLEMENTED (harvest.rs:541) but NEVER CALLED in production — weight_for always passes surprisal=1.0. This is the 'Implemented But Not Wired' failure mode at the architectural level. FIX: With metabolic delta-crystallization, urgency reduces to sum(tx/delta-crystallization for tx since harvest). Transactions that move coherence up are worth protecting. Routine operations score near-zero. Alert fatigue dies because urgency measures information content, not transaction volume. TRACES TO: INV-HARVEST-005 (proactive warning), NEG-HARVEST-001 (false warning rate), INV-GUIDANCE-019 (adaptive threshold).; Session entity: :recon/trace-7f1462d1ef414cd7; Session entity: :recon/trace-f86cda65f73997aa; Session entity: :recon/trace-f218289be3e6cf3a; Session entity: :recon/trace-3f30cd1b8688e600; THREE-BOUNDARY-COHERENCE-VECTOR: The complete metabolic signature is three components, one per boundary: (1) delta-crystallization (Intent↔Spec): positive when observations crystallize into spec elements, negative when observations are created without spec connection. (2) delta-implementation (Spec↔Impl): positive when spec elements get implemented, negative when unanchored implementation added. (3) delta-verification (Impl↔Behavior): positive when witnesses registered, negative when implementation exists without verification. These three components answer 'where is knowledge stuck in the pipeline?' Each maps to a reconciliation type: delta-cryst=Epistemic, delta-impl=Structural, delta-verif=Behavioral. PRIORITY INSIGHT: delta-crystallization should be implemented FIRST because it measures the only boundary with ZERO existing coverage. Delta-implementation and delta-verification have partial coverage via trace scanning, witness system, and bilateral loop. Intent↔Spec has nothing. HEBBIAN-BAYESIAN SYNTHESIS: Hebbian (bottom-up) = entities co-occurring in high-novelty transactions get stronger associations, building a salience map. Bayesian (top-down) = seed assembles prior, transactions provide evidence, posterior updates, coherence-delta measures prediction error. Together: one builds the map, the other navigates it. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-HARVEST-001, INV-SEED-001, ADR-GUIDANCE-002 (basin competition).; F-S-INERTIA-AND-WITNESS-GAP: F(S) stuck at 0.67 despite 41 tasks closed. Root cause: 252 INVs are 'untested' (no L2+ FBW witness). But 1,568 tests EXIST covering most invariants — they just don't explicitly reference INV IDs. The gap is registration not testing. The trace scanner requires explicit '// Verifies: INV-STORE-001' comments. FIX TWO-PART: (1) Enhance trace scanner to also match function names containing INV namespace (test_append_only → INV-STORE-001), proptest functions testing described properties, test file doc comments. (2) With metabolic delta-verification (Impl↔Behavior boundary), every witness registration transaction updates F(S) incrementally instead of requiring batch bilateral scan. F(S) stops being inert. ALSO: delta-crystallization feeds into this because better formalized observations → more spec elements → more targets for witness registration → F(S) improves. TRACES TO: INV-WITNESS-001 (triple-hash binding), INV-WITNESS-006 (test body hash extraction), INV-BILATERAL-001 (bilateral convergence).; REACTIVE-TASK-CLOSURE: 44% of Session 030 work (18/41 tasks) was verifying already-implemented tasks and closing them. Root cause: task system is open-loop — no feedback from store to tasks. Tasks created by observation, closed only by explicit agent action. When implementation happens as side-effect of other work, task stays open indefinitely. FIX: Harvest-integrated reconciliation sweep — extend braid harvest --commit to auto-close tasks whose acceptance criteria are store-verifiable, in same atomic transaction. Uses existing audit_tasks_from_store (confidence >= 0.7 threshold). Records completion_method :task.completion/harvest-reconciliation. Piggybacks on existing ceremony (harvest) rather than adding new one — the agent already runs harvest, so zero additional process obligation. The harvest pipeline already shows top-5 audit results (line 268 of harvest.rs) — the gap is: it displays but doesn't close. DEPENDENCY: Benefits from delta-crystallization because better formalized observations → better spec anchoring → better audit confidence scores → more accurate auto-close. TRACES TO: INV-TASK-006 (completion evidence protocol), INV-HARVEST-001 (harvest monotonicity), INV-BILATERAL-002 (five-point coherence).; DOG-FOOD ASSESSMENT: Grade B+. Core abstractions work (harvest/seed, R(t), P(t)). Three improvements needed: (1) novelty-weighted harvest urgency to eliminate alert fatigue, (2) verification-and-closure automation (audit --auto-close), (3) session-progress dashboard. Key insight: 44% of work was verification not implementation — system needs first-class verification mode. Key tension: task management (70% of interactions) has less polish than knowledge management (the designed use case).; REALTIME-CRYSTALLIZATION-FEEDBACK: The highest-impact single change: show delta-crystallization in the braid observe command output in real time. Currently braid observe feels like writing into a void — observation goes into store, no metric changes, no signal fires. The radical move: close the feedback loop at the point of creation, not at the point of review. When agent runs braid observe, the system immediately: (1) computes delta-crystallization for this transaction, (2) if negative (unanchored), runs spec_relevance_scan to find nearest spec element, (3) suggests crystallization command inline. This transforms observe from write-only to dialogue. NEUROSCIENCE PARALLEL: This IS hippocampal pattern completion — at moment of encoding, compare against existing memories, signal novelty vs familiarity. Agent doesn't need to remember to check for crystallization gaps; store tells them at maximum-context moment. WHAT DIES: (a) Crystallization backlog — decisions happen at observe time with fresh context, not at harvest with stale context. (b) Ceremony gap between observe and crystallize — output of observe directly suggests spec create command, two operations become single cognitive unit. (c) Alert fatigue from methodology gaps — per-observation decisions replace aggregate warning. IMPLEMENTATION: ~20 lines in commands/observe.rs. Uses existing spec_relevance_scan. Delta computation same as full metabolic system but shown immediately rather than stored silently. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-014 (contextual observation funnel), INV-GUIDANCE-024 (knowledge reconciliation completeness), INV-HARVEST-005 (proactive warning).; Session entity: :recon/trace-f8740c0bf4cf7f85; METABOLIC-FOUNDATION: The store needs a metabolism — continuous, autonomous semantic computation at write time. Currently the store is passive (datoms go in, nothing comes out unless agent asks). Every process obligation (observe, harvest, reconcile, audit) is a ceremony the agent must remember, and ceremonies decay under pressure. The radical insight: make transact() self-aware. After committing datoms, the store examines what happened and annotates the transaction entity with derived metadata. This inverts the information architecture from 'agent observes world → agent writes datoms → store stores them' to 'agent writes datoms → store stores them → store observes what happened → store writes metadata'. The store becomes its own first observer. This is the store comonad principle from Session 029 made literal. ALGEBRAIC: Transaction digests are morphism annotations — metadata about the arrows in the category (Store, transact). They form a natural transformation from the raw-store functor to the annotated-store functor, enriching every morphism with semantic metadata while preserving categorical structure (composition, identity, merge as coproduct). ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLE: Move semantic computation from query time to write time. The store already maintains EAVT/AEVT/VAET/AVET structural indexes at write time. Metabolic transactions extend this to semantic indexes (coherence, novelty, cross-references) at write time. COST: ~5 extra datoms per transaction (~40% growth). At 31k datoms and ~100 tx/session, this is negligible for years. TRACES TO: SEED.md §4 (datom abstraction), SEED.md §7 (self-improvement loop), INV-STORE-014 (every store interaction is an observation).\nSession entity: :task/t-ba14c7a9; Session entity: :task/t-b394164e; Session entity: :task/t-aeb41600; Session entity: :task/t-1a2a36e2; Session entity: :task/t-c84db3d3; Session entity: :task/t-f2d25acc; Session entity: :task/t-af422045; Session entity: :task/t-a5972034; Session entity: :task/t-704de6b3; Session entity: :task/t-b4647ba9" :op :assert}
